The paper discusses security implications of modular learning components (MLCs) in machine learning systems, indicating a focus on cybersecurity (cs.CR). The paper also explores the feasibility of attacks on two state-of-the-art ML systems, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper discusses potential countermeasures to mitigate MLC-based attacks, indicating a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and system integration (cs.SI).
